!); 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FEB7FC42FE7EBFE7" box="[329,495,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">Thomas 14624</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="ED18AE4992417723FE00FC42FDF0BFE7" box="[510,609,914,940]" country="Brazil" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15526" name="CEPEC, CEPLAC" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" type="Herbarium">CEPEC</collectionCode>
!).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB6368C92417723FF43FC66FD83B877" blockId="17.[136,1452,158,1480]" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FF43FC66FE29BF9B" bold="true" box="[189,440,950,976]" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FE46FC67FE40BF9B" box="[440,465,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">—</emphasis>
There are only two known populations of the species, but most specimens were found in “Fazenda Duas Barras” (
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92417723FE62FC0AFDA6BFBE" box="[412,567,986,1013]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
), an area of primary forest inside the “Parque Nacional Alto Cariri”. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92417723FACAFC0AFE91B853" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kollmannii">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FACAFC0AFE91B853" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">Bertolonia kollmannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an EOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992417723FE42FC2EFD94B850" box="[444,517,1022,1051]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" unit="km" value="82.0">82 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992417723FD54FC2EFC92B850" box="[682,771,1022,1051]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.01" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" unit="km" value="201.0">201 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Critically Endangered” (CR), following 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92417723FF02FBF2FE03B877" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[252,402,1058,1084]" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C313650792417723FF43FB96FF73B983" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB6368C92417723FF43FB96FF73B983" blockId="17.[136,1452,158,1480]" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FF43FB96FE98B82B" bold="true" box="[189,265,1094,1120]" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92417723FED8FB96FD8DB82B" box="[294,540,1094,1120]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kollmannii">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FED8FB96FD8DB82B" box="[294,540,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">Bertolonia kollmannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in a restricted area along the border between the states of 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92417723FB11FB96FAA1B82B" box="[1263,1328,1094,1120]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">Bahia</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92417723FA9BFB96FF45B8CF" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, in montane rainforests (
<figureCitation id="13322A0992417723FE1BFBBAFDA6B8CE" box="[485,567,1130,1157]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[341,1239,654,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-255@5.[340,1247,641,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A. Bertolonia alternifolia. B. Bertolonia angustipetala. C. Bertolonia bullata. D. Bertolonia carmoi. E. Bertolonia cuspidata. F. Bertolonia hirsutissima. G. Bertolonia igrapiuna. H. Bertolonia kollmannii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597686/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">Fig. 3h</figureCitation>
), in moist and shaded slopes near water. Collected with flowers in February and August, with fruits in February, April and August. The species can be recognized by the small, ovate and bullate leaf blades with an acute apex and crenate margins, flowers with fimbriate sepals, pink petals with the apex not apiculate and anthers dehiscing through an extrorse pore. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92417723FD5FFB06FC09B8BB" box="[673,920,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kollmannii">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FD5FFB06FC09B8BB" box="[673,920,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">Bertolonia kollmannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92417723FBD7FB07FF2FB95E" authority="Baumgratz (1990: 125)" authorityName="Baumgratz" authorityPageNumber="125" authorityYear="1990" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wurdackiana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FBD7FB07FB48B8BB" box="[1065,1241,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">B. wurdackiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92417723FB1FFB07FF2FB95E" author="Baumgratz, J. F. A." pageId="17" pageNumber="170" pagination="69 - 213" refId="ref18783" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A. (1990) O genero Bertolonia Raddi (Melastomataceae): revisao taxonomica e consideracoes anatomicas. Arquivos do Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro - Serie Botanica 30: 69 - 213." type="journal article" year="1990">Baumgratz (1990: 125)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, endemic of the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92417723FE34FB2AFDFDB95F" box="[458,620,1274,1300]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92417723FD88FB2AFCFDB95F" box="[630,876,1274,1300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kollmannii">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FD88FB2AFCFDB95F" box="[630,876,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">Bertolonia kollmannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the usually smaller leaf blades (2.4–5.5 × 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992417723FF76FACEFE96B972" box="[136,263,1310,1337]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.15" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" unit="cm" value="3.15" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="1.6">1.6–4.7 cm</quantity>
) with an acute apex and crenate margins (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FD1CFACFFD68B973" box="[738,761,1311,1336]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">vs</emphasis>
. usually bigger leaf blades (5.8–15 × 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992417723FB5DFACEFB68B972" box="[1187,1273,1310,1337]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" unit="cm" value="5.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="3.0">3–8 cm</quantity>
) with an obtuse or rounded apex and serrate margins in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92417723FDB8FA93FD67B917" authorityName="Baumgratz" authorityYear="1990" box="[582,758,1346,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wurdackiana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FDB8FA93FD67B917" box="[582,758,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">B. wurdackiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), by the pink, 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992417723FC65FA92FB9CB916" box="[923,1037,1346,1373]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" unit="mm" value="6.25" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.5">5.5–7 mm</quantity>
long petals, with an obtuse apex (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FA73FA93FA3AB917" box="[1421,1451,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">vs.</emphasis>
white petals, 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992417723FEE4FAB6FE0EB9CA" box="[282,415,1382,1409]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.05" metricValueMax="8.3" metricValueMin="7.8" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" unit="mm" value="8.05" valueMax="8.3" valueMin="7.8">7.8–8.3 mm</quantity>
long, with an acute and dorsally apiculate apex) and cream-colored anthers dehiscing through an extrorse pore (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FEB0FA5BFEFDB9EF" box="[334,364,1419,1444]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">vs.</emphasis>
yellow anthers dehiscing through an introrse pore). For more details, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92417723FB54FA5AFAEDB9EF" author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[1194,1404,1418,1445]" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92417723FB0FFA5BFAB2B9EF" box="[1265,1315,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation id="C68B033792417723FF76FA7EFF4DB983" box="[136,220,1454,1480]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2" pageId="17" pageNumber="170" tableUuid="DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
